<subSubSection id="24DC108B5E60C52FFF3FBE10FBC0ECC7" pageId="98" pageNumber="99" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="6C7943005E60C52FFF3FBE10FBC0ECC7" blockId="98.[151,1436,151,428]" pageId="98" pageNumber="99">
<emphasis id="5EB29F125E60C52FFF3FBE10FE97EC77" bold="true" box="[199,321,259,284]" pageId="98" pageNumber="99">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
One of the 
<taxonomicName id="ABC638835E60C52FFE30BE17FD8AEC77" box="[456,604,260,284]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Pygatyphella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="98" pageNumber="99" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="5EB29F125E60C52FFE30BE17FD8AEC77" box="[456,604,260,284]" italics="true" pageId="98" pageNumber="99">Pygatyphella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
B complex of 
<bibRefCitation id="08573EF15E60C52FFCFDBE17FBA6EC77" author="Ballantyne, L. A. &amp; Lambkin, C. L." box="[773,1136,260,284]" pageId="98" pageNumber="99" refId="ref122754" refString="Ballantyne, L. A. &amp; Lambkin, C. L. (2009) Systematics of Indo-Pacific fireflies with a redefinition of Australasian Atyphella Olliff, Madagascan Photuroluciola Pic, and description of seven new genera from the Luciolinae (Coleoptera: Lampyridae)." type="book" year="2009">Ballantyne and Lambkin (2009)</bibRefCitation>
; dorsal colouration orange pronotum with dark brown elytra which are pale margined along their lateral margins; most similar to 
<taxonomicName id="ABC638835E60C52FFA91BE3AFE6FEC0F" authority="(Ballantyne)" baseAuthorityName="Ballantyne" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Pygatyphella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="98" pageNumber="99" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="limbatifusca">
<emphasis id="5EB29F125E60C52FFA91BE3AFEF4EC0F" italics="true" pageId="98" pageNumber="99">Pac. limbatifusca</emphasis>
(Ballantyne)
</taxonomicName>
, distinguished by the absence of small paired dark markings on the pronotum, the very dark brown elytra and the narrower lateral pale band. 
<bibRefCitation id="08573EF15E60C52FFD16BE7CFB85ECEC" author="Ballantyne, L. A. &amp; Lambkin, C. L." box="[750,1107,367,391]" pageId="98" pageNumber="99" refId="ref122754" refString="Ballantyne, L. A. &amp; Lambkin, C. L. (2009) Systematics of Indo-Pacific fireflies with a redefinition of Australasian Atyphella Olliff, Madagascan Photuroluciola Pic, and description of seven new genera from the Luciolinae (Coleoptera: Lampyridae)." type="book" year="2009">Ballantyne and Lambkin (2009)</bibRefCitation>
distinguished this from other similarly coloured species on page 69 and from 
<emphasis id="5EB29F125E60C52FFD49BE86FCA4ECC7" box="[689,882,404,428]" italics="true" pageId="98" pageNumber="99">
Pygat. 
<taxonomicName id="ABC638835E60C52FFCF8BE87FCA4ECC7" authorityName="Olivier" authorityYear="1911" box="[768,882,404,428]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Atyphella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="98" pageNumber="99" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="salomonis">salomonis</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
in 
<tableCitation id="214476BB5E60C52FFC6DBE87FC22ECC7" box="[917,1012,404,428]" captionStart="TABLE 8" captionStartId="43.[151,239,873,897]" captionText="TABLE 8. SE Asian and Australopacific Luciolinae described as Luciola spp. (sensu McDermott 1966) with orange" pageId="98" pageNumber="99">Tables 8</tableCitation>
, 
<tableCitation id="214476BB5E60C52FFBF9BE87FBC7ECC7" box="[1025,1041,404,428]" captionStart="TABLE 9" captionStartId="54.[151,239,295,319]" captionText="TABLE 9. Luciolinae males with dark brown, grey or black dorsal colouration." pageId="98" pageNumber="99">9</tableCitation>
.
</paragraph>
